## VULNERABILITY CLASSES (MANDATORY)

Check every file for every class below.

====================================================================
CRITICAL
====================================================================

CRIT-1: IDOR on entity IDs
- Any action/query taking IDs from `args` must fetch entity and immediately verify ownership/authorization.
- Financial entities must not allow cross-account operations.
- Return 403 on unauthorized access after entity lookup.

Must-check functions/areas:
- `applyWalletToEscrow`, `requestWalletWithdrawal`, `getBrandEscrowDetails`
- `createRazorpayOrder`, `verifyRazorpayPayment`, `deleteDraftDrop`
- `submitOrderProof`, `submitVideoLink`, `brandVerifyOrder`
- `getDropApplications`, `getBrandWallet`, `getAdminWithdrawalQueue`
- `getCreatorBankDetails`, `saveCreatorBankDetails`
- `adminProcessCreatorPayout`
- `getScreenshotDownloadUrl` (key must belong to exact application)

CRIT-2: Missing `auth: true` in `main.wasp`
- Private actions/queries without `auth: true` are high-risk misconfigurations.
- Especially all money-moving actions and admin-only actions.

CRIT-3: Raw `context.user` auth logic bypassing hardened wrappers
- Flag direct role/id checks if function does not first call hardened helper.
- Treat as critical when in financial/admin operations.

CRIT-4: Privilege escalation from client-controlled role/admin fields
- Any write path accepting `role`, `isAdmin`, `adminRole`, `approvalStatus` from `args` is critical.
- Verify super-admin gating for role assignment actions.

CRIT-5: Race conditions on balance checks
- Balance check outside transaction is exploitable.
- Verify check + debit + ledger + audit are atomic.
- Verify duplicate pending-withdrawal prevention is atomic.

CRIT-6: Float arithmetic on money
- Flag JS number math on money persistence logic.
- Require `Prisma.Decimal` arithmetic end-to-end.

CRIT-7: Dev backdoors in production path
- `makeMeAdminByEmail`, seed/debug endpoints, dev auth bypasses.
- Any temporary privilege utility still declared in `main.wasp`.

CRIT-8: Razorpay amount not server-verified against DB
- Order amount must come from DB escrow state, never client amount.
- Post-signature verify must compare Razorpay amount with expected owed amount.
- Webhook must verify HMAC using raw body before processing.

====================================================================
SERIOUS
====================================================================

SERIOUS-1: Unvalidated enums/decision strings
- Any state-driving string must be strict whitelist validated.

SERIOUS-2: Sensitive data overexposure in responses
- Non-owner/non-admin must never receive raw bank/UPI/account details.
- Use `select` projections, not full model returns.

SERIOUS-3: Sensitive data in logs/audit descriptions
- Raw account numbers/UPI IDs must be masked before logs/audit blobs.

SERIOUS-4: Missing transaction bundling on financial updates
- Balance update + ledger + audit must be one `prisma.$transaction`.

SERIOUS-5: S3 key injection/unauthorized file access
- Key from args must be validated against owned/authorized record.

SERIOUS-6: Unsanitized/unbounded input
- URL sanitization, finite positive numeric checks, length caps.
- Prevent negative amount exploits and storage abuse.

====================================================================
MODERATE
====================================================================

MOD-1: Status-machine violations and replayable terminal transitions
MOD-2: Bank-detail changes invalidating payout safety snapshots
MOD-3: Unbounded queries / N+1 DoS vectors
MOD-4: Error detail leakage (Prisma internals, stack traces, entity existence)
MOD-5: Webhook idempotency gaps (duplicate event processing)
MOD-6: Manual admin credit cap missing
MOD-7: Hardcoded financial constants in frontend instead of server config

====================================================================
LOW
====================================================================

LOW-1: Sensitive `console.log` in production path
LOW-2: Source maps exposing source in production
LOW-3: Deprecated/unused but still exposed operations in `main.wasp`
LOW-4: Missing rate limits on high-risk endpoints
LOW-5: `any` types in financial paths reducing static safety


